rComments: She's very difficult to follow in class. Did not learn much in her class. Very tough marker!

Dorothy was probably the sweetest, lovely prof I've ever had. She is obviously extremely knowledgable, and goes to incredible lengths to make sure you're getting as much out of the class as possible. She's extremely responsive to feedback--during midterms we filled out some suggestion evaluations, and she amended everything mentioned. Awesome.

Not only were all her lectures dry and devoid of any insight or critical analysis, she was very dismissive when asked to go into a bit more depth at an office hours appointment.  She comes across as very rude and entitled, and was NOT at all what I was expecting.  Maybe she wrote all those reviews herself on June 23rd because the truth hurts.
I have doubts that two separate people chose to use the exact same phrase "impart her knowledge" when providing positive reviews. Coincidence?

I find it quite interesting that all of the good comments were posted on the same day. My experience in this class was very poor. I felt as though it was a lot of demographic information and I felt like the information was not being appropriately linked back to policy. I did not feel supported as a student by this professor.
